Search for missing Khayalethu Magadla continues. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Search operations to recover little Khayalethu Magadla are continuing. READ: Search continues for missing Soweto boy Robots have been deployed to help find the six-year old boy who fell into a manhole on Sunday. Family spokesperson, Veli Terra Mthethwa says they've accepted he's unlikely to have survived. Mthethwa said, "as the family now, we wish they could find his remains, we have accepted that theres a possibility he might not come out alive since he went missing on Sunday until today. We have accepted any outcome, we just want to find his remains.”